    "narrative": "For the Austin Waves on this April 16th slate, **Jackson Merrill** (67.22) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.90) emerge as our primary offensive anchors. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a highly favorable spot in the two-hole against a vulnerable Luis Castillo, with the projection model capitalizing on his right-handed platoon advantage to push his efficiency well into the \"Strong\" tier. Meanwhile, **Jacob Wilson** draws a lucrative matchup against Leiter; he is a priority play today because the park factors and current SP skill metrics align to boost his base projection by over 10 points, making him an essential piece for our daily Roto output. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.81) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.68) also provide solid stability, with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** specifically anchored by an excellent xwOBA of .384, suggesting he remains undervalued despite the moderate difficulty of the Sproat matchup.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved keeping **Nolan Schanuel** on the bench. While his score of 47.95 was respectable, the optimizer favored the higher ceilings of our active starters against weaker opposing arms. **Nolan Schanuel** ultimately lost out to **Miguel Vargas**, who holds a slightly better edge in batting order efficiency (leadoff spot), and **Josh Jung**, whose park factor adjustments provided just enough variance to keep him in the starting lineup. Looking at the bench, we must also maintain caution regarding **Gunnar Henderson**. While he remains a core part of our roster, his score of 48.62 is suppressed by a negative platoon split against the lefty Messick and a looming 44% rain risk. We will monitor the weather in his game closely, as any significant delays could impact his availability for this critical 5x5 push.",
